<paragraph blockId="23.[192,1440,1644,1929]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,338,1644,1668]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Definition.</emphasis>
A genus more related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Holland" authorityYear="1896" box="[639,723,1645,1668]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Gamia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[639,723,1645,1668]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Gamia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<collectingCountry box="[729,830,1645,1669]" name="Netherlands" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Holland</collectingCountry>
, 1896 (
<typeStatus box="[914,968,1645,1669]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Holland" authorityYear="1891" box="[1066,1255,1644,1668]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Proteides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="galua">
<emphasis box="[1066,1255,1644,1668]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Proteides galua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<collectingCountry box="[1260,1361,1645,1669]" name="Netherlands" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Holland</collectingCountry>
, 1891) and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Holland" authorityYear="1896" box="[245,358,1677,1700]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Artitropa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[245,358,1677,1700]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Artitropa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<collectingCountry box="[366,467,1677,1701]" name="Netherlands" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Holland</collectingCountry>
, 1896 (
<typeStatus box="[553,607,1677,1701]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Trimen, 1862" authorityName="Trimen" authorityYear="1862" box="[708,1098,1677,1701]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pamphila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erynnis">
<emphasis box="[708,926,1677,1701]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Pamphila erynnis</emphasis>
Trimen, 1862
</taxonomicName>
) than to 
<taxonomicName authority="Evans, 1937" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1937" box="[1208,1440,1677,1701]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Leona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1208,1282,1678,1701]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Leona</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Evans" box="[1290,1440,1677,1701]" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" refId="ref27329" refString="Evans, W. H. 1937. A catalogue of the African Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum. British Museum (Natural History); London. xii + 212 p., 30 pl." type="book" year="1937">Evans, 1937</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[200,253,1710,1734]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Plotz, 1879" authorityName="Plotz" authorityYear="1879" box="[351,694,1709,1734]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Hesperia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leonora">
<emphasis box="[351,555,1709,1733]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Hesperia leonora</emphasis>
Pl√∂tz, 1879
</taxonomicName>
) (
<figureCitation box="[717,787,1710,1734]" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="22.[192,275,1419,1441]" captionTargetBox="[193,1440,215,1384]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[192,1440,213,1385]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Figure 9. Genomic trees of Astictopterini and relatives. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677253" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677253/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). Keys to VIII.59.C(b) in 
<bibRefCitation author="Evans" box="[1083,1241,1710,1734]" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" refId="ref27329" refString="Evans, W. H. 1937. A catalogue of the African Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum. British Museum (Natural History); London. xii + 212 p., 30 pl." type="book" year="1937">Evans (1937)</bibRefCitation>
and differs from its relatives, including 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1937" box="[473,547,1742,1765]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Leona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[473,547,1742,1765]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Leona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by a well-defined gnathos reaching about half of uncus length (in lateral view); tegumen plus uncus twice as long as wide, hour-glass shaped in ventral view; uncus divided, arms short and stout, knob-like; valva with harpe close to rectangular; hindwing with a postdiscal band of spots above. In DNA, a combination of the following base pairs is diagnostic: aly127.66.15: 
<specimenCode box="[1352,1413,1839,1863]" collectionCode="T" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">T199</specimenCode>
A, aly 
<date box="[230,341,1872,1896]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" value="1149-01-01">1149.1.1</date>
:A1727G, aly822.30.12:A417C, aly490.3.1:A60A (not G), aly6339.4.1:G167G (not T), aly 
<date box="[228,335,1904,1928]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" value="1121-03-02">1121.3.2</date>
:C344C (not T).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
